[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671004\">@Danilo Krummrich</span> has a use-case for references to already initialized fields within the initializer macros. <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"519727\">@Alice Ryhl</span> also said this to be useful at RustWeek. I also think it's useful, but I fear that this is a footgun, since any raw pointer derived from such a reference-to-a-field might get invalidated upon using a reference to the entire struct.</p>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>Example</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span><span class=\"n\">marker</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PhantomPinned</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span><span class=\"n\">pin_data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceInit</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Debug)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SelfWriter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_pin</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PhantomPinned</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SelfWriter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">write2</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_inner_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">main</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SelfWriter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// this would be generated by the macro, so one could just write `ptr: val` here</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// instead.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">()).</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">val</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_pin</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PhantomPinned</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">42</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write2</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">82</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">42</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>$ cargo miri run --example demo\nSelfWriter { val: 0, ptr: 0x237e0, _pin: PhantomPinned }\nSelfWriter { val: 42, ptr: 0x237e0, _pin: PhantomPinned }\nSelfWriter { val: 82, ptr: 0x237e0, _pin: PhantomPinned }\nerror: Undefined Behavior: attempting a write access using &lt;1564&gt; at alloc814[0x8], but that tag does not exist in the borrow stack for this location\n  --&gt; examples/demo.rs:16:18\n   |\n16 |         unsafe { self.ptr.write(val) };\n   |                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n   |                  |\n   |                  attempting a write access using &lt;1564&gt; at alloc814[0x8], but that tag does not exist in the borrow stack for this location\n   |                  this error occurs as part of an access at alloc814[0x8..0x9]\n   |\n   = help: this indicates a potential bug in the program: it performed an invalid operation, but the Stacked Borrows rules it violated are still experimental\n   = help: see https://github.com/rust-lang/unsafe-code-guidelines/blob/master/wip/stacked-borrows.md for further information\nhelp: &lt;1564&gt; was created by a SharedReadWrite retag at offsets [0x8..0x9]\n  --&gt; examples/demo.rs:26:13\n   |\n26 |       let x = pin_init!(&amp;this in SelfWriter {\n   |  _____________^\n27 | |         val: 0,\n28 | |         ptr: {\n...  |\n34 | |         _pin: PhantomPinned,\n35 | |     });\n   | |______^\nhelp: &lt;1564&gt; was later invalidated at offsets [0x8..0x9] by a write access\n  --&gt; examples/demo.rs:21:9\n   |\n21 |         this.val = val;\n   |         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n   = note: BACKTRACE (of the first span):\n   = note: inside `SelfWriter::write` at examples/demo.rs:16:18: 16:37\nnote: inside `main`\n  --&gt; examples/demo.rs:42:5\n   |\n42 |     x.as_mut().write(42);\n   |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n   = note: this error originates in the macro `$crate::__init_internal` which comes from the expansion of the macro `pin_init` (in Nightly builds, run with -Z macro-backtrace for more info)\n\nnote: some details are omitted, run with `MIRIFLAGS=-Zmiri-backtrace=full` for a verbose backtrace\n\nerror: aborting due to 1 previous error\n</code></pre></div>\n</div></div>\n<p>If I use <code>UnsafePinned</code> in the example, then it does continue to work:</p>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>Example with UnsafePinned</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#![feature(unsafe_pinned)]</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">UnsafePinned</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span><span class=\"n\">pin_data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceInit</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Debug)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SelfWriter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">UnsafePinned</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SelfWriter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">write2</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map_unchecked_mut</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_mut_pinned</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">main</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SelfWriter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">UnsafePinned</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// this would be generated by the macro, so one could just write `ptr:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// val.get_mut_pinned()` here instead.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">()).</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_mut_pinned</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">42</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write2</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">82</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">42</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"fm\">println!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>$ cargo miri run --example demo\nSelfWriter { val: UnsafePinned { .. }, ptr: 0x237e0 }\nSelfWriter { val: UnsafePinned { .. }, ptr: 0x237e0 }\nSelfWriter { val: UnsafePinned { .. }, ptr: 0x237e0 }\nSelfWriter { val: UnsafePinned { .. }, ptr: 0x237e0 }\n</code></pre></div>\n</div></div>\n<p>Before I go to t-opsem, I thought I'd ask here for people's opinion. I fear that people might get the wrong impression what these references would be for. But since it works well with <code>UnsafePinned</code>, it might not be a problem?</p>",
        "id": 521255949,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748597320
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span></p>",
        "id": 521255997,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748597338
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would say <code>UnsafePinned</code> is exactly for cases like this.</p>",
        "id": 521317536,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1748618015
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yea, I think this is expected</p>",
        "id": 521341948,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1748626309
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Writing directly to val would invalidate the ptr</p>",
        "id": 521342069,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1748626348
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You get this without pin-init, with just structs on stack too</p>",
        "id": 521342534,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1748626559
